{"id":"12868","name":"Share via Snapdrop (draft base64)","tagline":"Shortcut to \"Snapdrop\" from share sheet","icon":"ios15 c463140863 g61501","latest":"34696","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><b><a href=\"https://snapdrop.net\">Snapdrop</a></b> is a sublime <b>alternative to AirDrop</b>.\nIt uses peer to peer connection in the same local network/wifi to send images, documents or text. As it is web based, it runs on every device.</p>\n<p>Perfect for sharing urls and texts between devices and platforms.</p>\n<p>Works with photos as well.</p>\n<p>This is a draft version which waits for a pull request to be merged:\nhttps://github.com/RobinLinus/snapdrop/pull/488\nWhen merged, this shortcut will trigger paste mode on snapdrop.net automatically and insert files and photos as data-uri.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<h2>How to use:</h2>\n\n<h5>on receiver device (Laptop): </h5>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Open https://snapdrop.net</li>\n</ol>\n<h5>on sender device (iOS): </h5>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Visit website or open image etc.</li>\n<li>Open share sheet and select the Snapdrop shortcut</li>\n<li>Shortcut saves input to clipboard and opens snapdrop.net</li>\n<li>Tap the receiver device to send clipboard directly</li>\n</ol>\n<p><br>\n<br>\n</p><h5>Tipp:</h5>\nTo have the shortcut always on top, go to the bottom of a share sheet, click \"edit actions\" and add the Snapdrop shortcut to your favorites.<p></p>\n<p><br><br>\n</p><h5>Tipp2:</h5>\n Snapdrop is a webapp and can installed on all machines as a cached version.<p></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.2-beta - Aug. 24, 2022, 2:14 p.m.</strong></p>"}